  "body": "### Component\n\nForge, Foundryup\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (249538f 2023-02-09T00:01:54.1537047Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n forge init hello_foundry\n\n### Operating System\n\nWindows\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAfter installing foundry as directed by the documentation, I used the command \"  forge init hello_foundry\"  to create a project and I got this error.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe target directory is a part of or on its own an already initialized git repository,\r\nand it requires clean working and staging areas, including no untracked files.\r\n\r\nCheck the current git repository's status with `git status`.\r\nThen, you can track files with `git add ...` and then commit them with `git commit`,\r\nignore them in the `.gitignore` file, or run this command again with the `--no-commit` flag.\r\n\r\nIf none of the previous steps worked, please open an issue at:\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/new/choose",
